5|$|From 1936 to 1945, {{the lion}} {{was once again}} {{replaced}} by an eagle, only this time the one of <b>the</b> <b>Nazi</b> party, the Reichsadler. Deemed the Hauptstadt der Bewegung (Capital of the Movement), Munich was a significant place in terms of <b>the</b> <b>Nazi</b> ideology. The city was home to the NSDAP headquarters, the Beer Hall Putsch and also saw the establishment of Dachau, the first Nazi concentration camp. Post-war designs were not pursued until 1949.|$|E
